description:
It's the national Day of Reconciliation and as much as we all enjoy a holiday, let’s not forget that today is a day to reflect and learn from the past. First up we are absolutely honoured to have a South African household name in the loft. Internationally renowned jazz musician and South Africa’s most iconic pianist and composer, Abdullah Ibrahim is in the country and joins us in the loft today. He’ll also be treating us to a live performance later in the show. 

We also have Analyst and Public Speaker on Gender, Politics, Leadership and Cultural Issues, Nomboniso Gasa, to give us some insight into where South Africa stands today with regards to the goals set when democracy was achieved in 1994.

http://afternoonexpress.co.za/
